<div style="text-align: right;"><div class="page-rate-widget-box"><span class="rate-points">rating:&nbsp;<span class="number prw54353">+33</span></span><span class="rateup btn btn-default"><a title="I like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, 1)">+</a></span><span class="ratedown btn btn-default"><a title="I don't like it" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.rate(event, -1)">&#8211;</a></span><span class="cancel btn btn-default"><a title="Cancel my vote" href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.modules.PageRateWidgetModule.listeners.cancelVote(event)">x</a></span></div></div>
<h1 id="toc0"><span><strong>Welcome</strong> to the <strong>Meatverse</strong></span></h1>
<h3 id="toc1"><span>Introduction</span></h3>
<p>Hello and welcome to my Author page! I first began reading the SCP Wiki in 2013 while trying to survive a night shift job at a data center. The first ever SCP I remember reading was <a href="/scp-087">SCP-087</a>: The Stairwell and it remains a personal favorite today. While my personal style differs greatly from some of those S1 works, it was far more than necessary to draw me in to this wonderful world.</p>
<p>Although I would not actually make an account for 3 more years and would not post my first SCP for another 2 beyond that, the SCP Wiki has remained a source of joy, inspiration, wonder, and community for me since the very beginning. Okay, enough sap.</p>
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/manymeats/tara.jpg" style="width:300px;" alt="tara.jpg" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;">
<p>SCP-MEAT's most powerful avatar</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/manymeats/otto.jpg" style="width:300px;" alt="otto.jpg" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;">
<p>Pontifex Canis Major</p>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id="toc2"><span>The Author</span></h3>
<p>I live in America's upper midwest region within a couple hours drive from Chicago, IL. In my off-site life, I am an IT professional and have been in that space almost exclusively for nearly 15 years. I room with three animals, none of which pay rent, and all are picture in the second image.</p>
<p>I love to cook with an especially profound love for Mediterranean fair (Italy, Southern France, Espagne, Greece). You'll also find me advocating for many SEA dishes, especially 'street food' or a good piece of fusion cuisine. I consider myself to be pretty well traveled and cooking things from different cultures is the quickest, cheapest way to either take myself back to where I've been, or imagine a new place or experience to have.</p>
<p>I love tabletop RPGs like D&amp;D 3rd Edition, Mage: The Ascension, and Scion, and other deep sets of systems with lots of books/content and loose rules. I have been GM'ing tabletop games since 2006 and have made some incredible memories!</p>
<p>I love supporting my favorite teams and sharing the energy of team sports. I was an athlete in both high school and college, and although I only regularly participate in golf and bowling privately today, I have been and will be a life-long fan for both college basketball and college football. Go Wisconsin Badgers! And Go Chicago Cubs!</p>
<h3 id="toc3"><span>The Colorful Cast</span></h3>
<p><strong>Tara</strong> is my rescue mutt who I adopted in October of 2016. She was sent to me from a high-kill shelter in the Houston area originally as a foster but I, of course, fell in love. She's high anxiety around strangers but the epitome of a loving animal. She's high energy and high activity which, although it frustrates me some days, helps me lazy ass out considerably.</p>
<p><strong>Ser Barristan Selmy</strong> is the white cat, named so for his bold personality, white hair, and wheat-gold tuft of hair on the crown of his head. Barristan is one member of a bonded pair of litter mates that I took in from a family who adopted a cat they did not know was pregnant. Although he has his claws, I have never met a more gentle set of cats with regards to their surprise attacks. They've never once assaulted my hands despite nearly 3 years of belly rubs!</p>
<p><strong>Grey Worm</strong> is the other half of the kitty-pair, the smoky gray cat. Yes, I did name him &quot;Grey Worm&quot; and then just describe the color as gray. He is far more soft-spoken and easy-going than his brother and loves to loaf around on the floor and in beams of sun from the windows. He is gentle like his brother and, despite his massive size, has one of the most smol and adorable meows of any adult cat I've ever heard.</p>
<p><strong>Otto</strong> was one of the most gentlemanly and distinguished pups I've ever had the pleasure of meeting. He came into my life in 2006 and lived 13 beautiful and happy years with me and then later my parents. Always impeccably groomed, his works were thoughtful and poignant and he loved to stay up with me late at night and watch Law and Order. I will miss you dearly, Mr. Otto.</p>
<h3 id="toc4"><span>The Inspiration</span></h3>
<p>Many of my personal inspirations involve dry humor and absurdism. While I would not go so far as to call anything I do truly surrealistic, I do often find myself creating imagery in my head that would qualify and pursuing thought experiments that cook the noggin in a similar fashion as that genre.</p>
<p>John Cleese, Douglar Adams, and Terry Pratchett are some of my favorite entertainers/authors. I'm a student of history although my degree is STEM, and I have been a flaired user on /r/AskHistorians since 2015 for the Roman Empire/Classical Europe. The Divine Comedy, The Discworld Series, and the Kingkiller Chronicle are my favorite written works. I enjoy numerous collections of short stories, particularly horror, but I find them difficult to defend for reasons other than my own visceral reaction.</p>
<p>Many of my favorite movies are comedies including Airplane, Space Balls, Blazing Saddles, Naked Gun, Animal House, Kung Pow: Enter the Fist, and Office Space. On the occasion I do nominate a more serious movie, it stands an equal chance of being either a powerful but well produced action film like John Wick or The Equalizer, or, it is likely to be an epic fantasy movie like Return of the King.</p>
<h4 id="toc5"><span>Table of Content</span></h4>
<p>Please enjoy a quick tour through my highest rated pieces. If you want to sample more of my works, you can find a collapsed table just below which is ordered by popularity. And hey, welcome to the Meatverse. I hope you enjoy your stay. After all, you're one of us.</p>
<div class="no-addendum">
<div class="no-footer">
<div class="unfolded-collapse">SCP-4497: Whose Cuisine Reigns Supreme?! [+166]</div>
<div class="unfolded-collapse-border">An esoteric adventure through the dream-scape of <a href="/scp-4497">SCP-4497</a>, this piece explores the ultimate power over cookery&#8230;if you have what it takes to defend the title!</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="no-addendum">
<div class="no-footer">
<div class="unfolded-collapse">SCP-5600: A December To Remember [+150]</div>
<div class="unfolded-collapse-border">My 5000 contest entry, <a href="/scp-5600">SCP-5600</a> takes us home to small-town Wisconsin for Christmas and never, ever lets us leave. Learning to let go on December 32nd.</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="no-addendum">
<div class="no-footer">
<div class="unfolded-collapse">SCP-5805: You Can't Go Back [+115]</div>
<div class="unfolded-collapse-border">Although one of my shortest works, <a href="/scp-5805">SCP-5805</a> packs a big punch aimed directly at a sense of loss and of nostalgia. The type of feeling that reminds you of summers past and friends no longer in your life, for whatever reason. This one's for you, Johnny. Wherever you are.</div>
</div>
</div>
<hr />
<div class="no-addendum">
<div class="no-footer">
<div class="unfolded-collapse">SCP-4486 Happy Is Relative [+96]</div>
<div class="unfolded-collapse-border">The legacy and history of Ronald McDonald is both goofy and very serious. <a href="/scp-4486">SCP-4486</a> explores a setting where the McDonald brothers created a friend to represent their love of their company and then lost control of him.</div>
</div>
</div>
